%html(lang="en-us")
  %head
    %meta(charset="UTF-8")
    %meta(name="description" content="A succinct reference in probability theory and statistics")
    %meta(name="keywords" content="Probability,Statistics,Reference,Cheatsheet,Cookbook")
    %meta(name="author" content="Matthias Vallentin")
    %meta(name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1")
    %title
      The Probability and Statistics Cookbook
    %link(rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="stylesheets/normalize.css" media="screen")
    %link(href='https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Open+Sans:400,700' rel='stylesheet' type='text/css')
    %link(rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="stylesheets/stylesheet.css" media="screen")
    %link(rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="stylesheets/github-light.css" media="screen")
  %body
    %section.page-header
      %h1.project-name The Probability and Statistics Cookbook
      %h2.project-tagline
      %a.btn(href="https://github.com/mavam/stat-cookbook/releases/download/0.1/stat-cookbook.pdf")
        Download PDF
      %a.btn(href="https://github.com/mavam/stat-cookbook")
        View on GitHub
    %section.main-content
      %p
        :markdown 
          The probability and statistics cookbook is a succinct representation
          of various topics in probability theory and statistics. It provides a
          comprehensive mathematical reference reduced to its essence, rather
          than aiming for elaborate explanations.

          The source code for this document is freely available on
          [github](https://github.com/mavam/stat-cookbook) and comes with a
          [Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 4.0 International
          License](http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/). 
      %h2
        %a#download.anchor{"aria-hidden" => "true", :href => "#download"}
          %span.octicon.octicon-link
        Download
      %p
        :markdown
          Latest release:

          - Version: [0.1](https://github.com/mavam/stat-cookbook/releases/tag/0.1)
          - Date: October 21, 2015

          Copyright &copy; [Matthias Vallentin](http://matthias.vallentin.net).
          To reproduce, please [contact me](http://matthias.vallentin.net).
      %h2
        %a#build.anchor{"aria-hidden" => "true", :href => "#build"}
          %span.octicon.octicon-link
        Build
      %p
        :markdown
          After cloning, you can build the cookbook locally via `make`. This
          first generates the distribution plots via R and then compiles the
          LaTeX source. You may have to install a few missing packages via
          CRAN.
